label: Machine Annotation Service
definition: A machine agent which will perform an action on the Digital Object potentially resulting in a new annotation on the object

label: ID
definition: Handle of the Machine Annotation Service

label: Type
definition: The DOI to the FDO type of the object

label: Status
definition: The status of the Digital Object

label: Version
definition: Version of the Machine Annotation Service, https://schema.org/version

label: Name
definition: Name of the Machine Annotation Service as provided by the user, https://schema.org/name

label: Description
definition: Description of the Machine Annotation Service as provided by the user, https://schema.org/description
examples: A service that links GBIF records to a DiSSCo Digital Specimen. It creates an EntityRelationship indicating the relationship

label: Date Created
definition: Timestamp of creation. Internally generated, https://schema.org/dateCreated

label: Date Modified
definition: Timestamp of last modification. Internally generated, https://schema.org/dateModified

label: Creator
definition: Contains an ods:Agent object

label: Container Image
definition: URI of the image of the containerized application

label: Container Tag
definition: Tag of the image

label: Target Digital Object Filter
definition: Filters describing the criteria that must be met in order to apply the MAS. No filters implies the MAS may run on *any* digital object. Field names are given in JSON paths, and accepted values for that field are provided as an arrays

label: Creative Work Status
definition: The current status of the service, https://schema.org/creativeWorkStatus

label: Code Repository
definition: Link to code base of MAS, https://schema.org/codeRepository

label: Programming Language
definition: The programming language of the MAS, https://schema.org/programmingLanguage

label: Service Availability
definition: Availability commitment of the service provider as described in the SLA

label: Maintainer
definition: Party maintaining the code, could be an schema:Organisation or a schema:Person

label: License
definition: License of the service, https://schema.org/license

label: Dependency
definition: Handles from other MAS that this MAS depends on

label: Contact Point
definition: The contact point for support and information for the MAS, https://schema.org/ContactPoint

label: Description
definition: Description of the contact point, https://schema.org/description

label: Email
definition: Email of the contact point, https://schema.org/email

label: URL
definition: Email of the contact point, https://schema.org/email

label: Telephone
definition: Telephone number of the contact point, https://schema.org/telephone

label: Sla Documentation
definition: Link to SLA documentation

label: Topic Name
definition: Kafka topic through which the MAS receives messages. Defaults to PID of MAS

label: Max Replicas
definition: The maximum amount of this MAS that can simultaneously run without causing issues

label: Batching Permitted
definition: Whether or not this MAS can create Batch Annotations. MAS outputs must then comply with batchMetadata, see https://schemas.dissco.tech/schemas/annotations/0.1.0/annotation-event.json

label: Time To Live
definition: Time in milliseconds the MAS message may remain in the Kafka Queue before being marked as timed out. Min 1 hour.

label: Tombstone Metadata
definition: Object containing the tombstone metadata of the object

label: Has Environmental Variable
definition: Environmental variables to supply to the MAS, non-sensitive

label: Has Secret Variable
definition: Secret variables to supply to the MAS

label: Tombstone Metadata
definition: The tombstone metadata about the tombstoned digital object, including the what, who and when of the tombstoning.

label: Tombstone Date
definition: Timestamp the Digital Object was tombstoned and no longer active.

label: Tombstone Text
definition: A reason why the Digital Object was tombstoned
examples: This is a duplicate of XXX| This object was made by mistake

label: Tombstoned By Agent
definition: The agent who tombstoned the object, contains an ods:Agent object

label: Has Related PID
definition: The PIDs of the object the tombstoned object is related to

label: Agent
definition: A generic agent class, containing information about the actor who performed an activity. This could be a person, an organization or a machine.

label: Name
definition: Full name of the agent

label: Role Name
definition: Indicates the role of the agent, https://schema.org/roleName

label: Start Date
definition: Date the agent began the role

label: End Date
definition: Date the agent ended the role

label: Role Order
definition: Order of the agent in the role. Can be used to indicate the order of importance

label: Email
definition: Email of the agent, can be present in case the agent is a maintainer of a MAS

label: URL
definition: URL of the agent, can be present in case the agent is a maintainer of a MAS

label: Has Identifier
definition: Contains zero or more ods:Identifier objects

label: Secret Variable
definition: A class containing information about which secret the Machine Annotation Service requires. The secret value will be supplied separately to DiSSCo.

label: Name
definition: The name of an environmental variable stored remotely

label: Secret Key Ref
definition: The name of the key stored in the secret store. NOT the secret's value.

label: Environmental Variable
definition: A class containing information about which (non-secret) environmental values the application requires.

label: Name
definition: The name of a non-sensitive property or environmental variable

label: Value
definition: Value to be stored in the "name" field. NOT for sensitive information.
